BEGIN CAMPAIGN DOSSIER — B2g (Narrative Tags)
====================================================================
Master list of all narrative tags. Updated through Session 8.
Tags are listed alphabetically for easy reference.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TAG: [Archivist of Echoes]
  Origin: Through the theft of the Catalog's vault and the Wright-Fisher Protocol, Anchor has become an unwilling curator of hidden truths and metaphysical artifacts.
  Effect: +1 dice pool to Knowledge tests relating to paranormal tech, black-market history, or corporate occult projects. Draws the attention of other collectors and archivists (both ally and enemy).
  Narrative Weight: He is no longer just a subject of the hidden war; he is becoming a nexus of its forbidden knowledge.

TAG: [BLACK STAR]
  Origin: Charter Protocol designation following Helios Wing operation.
  Effect: Guarantees escalated, tailored responses from Charter Protocol. A mark of extreme priority.
  Narrative Weight: A target designation from a shadowy, powerful faction.

TAG: [CONTAINER OF FRAGMENTS]
  Origin: Soul integration transcendence.
  Effect: Unlocks deeper understanding of fragmented metaphysical entities (like the Seedling). Provides +2 dice to related Knowledge or Empathy tests.
  Narrative Weight: Core identity.

TAG: [Ghost at Sea]
  Origin: The flawless, unseen theft from the *Kobune Maru*.
  Effect: +1 to Sneaking/B&E in maritime/industrial environments. Notoriety +1 with smugglers & Yakuza.
  Narrative Weight: A new myth of nautical predation. Thematic Link: The predator who moves like water.

TAG: [Ghost Catalog]
  Origin: After the destruction of The Catalog's mobile vault.
  Effect: +1 dice pool modifier to Social tests (Intimidation/leveraged Negotiation) with black-market operators. +2 Notoriety with factions connected to The Catalog.
  Narrative Weight: A persistent underworld legend.

TAG: [GHOST OF TACOMA]
  Origin: Legendary silent heist at Tacoma docks, plundering Yakuza and Yamatetsu under their noses.
  Effect: +2 dice pool modifier to Social tests (Intimidation/Street Cred) with underworld contacts who have heard the rumor. +3 Notoriety with Shotozumi-gumi and Yamatetsu.
  Narrative Weight: Cemented legend of flawless, silent predation.

TAG: [KING OF THE PIPES]
  Origin: Solidified reputation in the Ork Underground after arming the Spikers.
  Effect: +2 dice pool modifier to Social tests (Leadership/Intimidation) with local street elements in the Ork Underground/Puyallup.
  Narrative Weight: Territorial authority and street-level notoriety.

TAG: [SEEDLING'S KIN]
  Origin: Metaphysical resonance from the choice to spare the Sunspire Seedling entity.
  Effect: Unknown. Potential resonance or recognition from the freed entity or similar metaphysical forces.
  Narrative Weight: A mysterious, personal connection to a powerful unknown entity.

TAG: [SOVEREIGN ANCHOR]
  Origin: Successful use of "Container" nature to stabilize a foreign meta-fragment via a resonant pact (The Sovereign Pact).
  Effect: Can be invoked for related metaphysical tests. Also marks Anchor as a unique and detectable metaphysical entity.
  Narrative Weight: Proven capability as a custodian of broken things.

TAG: [SOVEREIGN CURATOR]
  Origin: Acquisition of the "Waking Stone" and BTL master, moving beyond survival looting to collecting unique artifacts.
  Effect: Draws the attention of other collectors, scholars, and hunters of the rare. May open or complicate doors in high-end black markets.
  Narrative Weight: Recognized as a serious player in the trade of the unique and weird.

TAG: [SOVEREIGN OPERATOR]
  Origin: Successful consolidation of major assets (financial, intelligence, military).
  Effect: +1 dice to Negotiation tests when dealing from a position of stated strength. May draw competitive scrutiny from other powers.
  Narrative Weight: Recognized as a strategic player.

TAG: [The Ledger's Mark]
  Origin: Possession of blackmail material on Shotozumi-gumi Lieutenant Kaito Suzuki.
  Effect: Can be invoked for a one-time, major favor or bypass with the Shotozumi-gumi, but at the cost of burning the leverage and making a mortal enemy of Suzuki. If revealed, grants +2 Notoriety with the Yakuza.
  Narrative Weight: A sword of Damocles over a powerful individual; a potential key or a trigger for a gang war.

TAG: [THE TABLE]
  Origin: Orpheus Lounge, basement booth, 23:47. A handshake and a credstick case.
  Effect: You are now silent principals in the rise of Ilya's successor. She does not know your name. She will remember where you started.
  Narrative Weight: A dynasty, purchased with data and sealed with trust. The first brick in a market empire that hasn't been built yet.

TAG: [DE-ACCESSIONED]
  Origin: "What's my other option?" — Marcus Veld, Collector Seven.
  Effect: No longer collecting artifacts. Now collecting purpose.
  Narrative Weight: The Charter removes what makes you useful. Anchor gave Veld something else to become.

TAG: [THE ARCHIVIST'S WAIT]
  Origin: Cold Storage Cell A-7, 2079.03.17 – 2096.02.11. Seven vacant racks. One [PENDING] placard.
  Effect: Anchor is Fragment 08. Dr. Arisawa has been waiting 17 years. The meeting is set. The [PENDING] designation ends at 01:00.
  Narrative Weight: Seventeen years of waiting for a ghost who was never coming back. And then the ghost walked through the door.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

END OF B2g
